That's pretty much how I use regen, and I pretty much  agree with your 
numbers
(although the max I have gotten is 20% (up/down the  same hill).  As you say
if traffic and road conditions permit you to  coast, that is what you want 
to
do, not slow down, which is what regen  does.  You wouldn't apply your
mechanical brakes in that situation, so  why would you apply regen?  I think
"coasting or regen" is the wrong  way to look at it.  Rather, the choice is
having controllable regen  capability so you can use it to slow or stop in
place of using mechanical  brakes, and in the same way, or not having 
regen.     



